average hydraulic oil temperature

This is the average temperature of the oil used in the gearbox of the wind turbine. It helps monitor the condition of the gearbox by tracking oil temperature. High temperatures may indicate potential issues with lubrication or internal components.

This is the average temperature of the bearings in the wind turbine gearbox. It helps monitor the condition of the bearings. High temperatures may indicate excessive friction or insufficient lubrication, which could lead to mechanical failure.

This represents the average temperature of the nacelle of the wind turbine. It helps monitor the overall temperature inside the nacelle, which houses critical components like the generator and gearbox. High temperatures could indicate overheating or potential issues with cooling systems.
